cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper focuses on predicting the dynamics of 3D rigid objects, which is a key area of research in robotics (cs.RO). The use of a neural network to represent object shape suggests a potential application in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the design of the network, which involves an understanding of physical laws, indicating a potential fit for machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the use of a physics engine to simulate object dynamics suggests a potential fit for graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
